                    <item_0
                        jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                        sling:resourceType="core/franklin/components/block/v1/block/item"
                        model="text-container-text"
                        modelFields="[text]"
                        name="Text Container Text"
                        text="&lt;p>We all know it: waste is a massive problem. And with more than &lt;a href=&quot;https://datatopics.worldbank.org/what-a-waste/trends_in_solid_waste_management.html&quot;>two billion&lt;/a> tons of solid waste produced globally according to the World Bank, there's no easy fix. But employees across AbbVie have been on a mission to ensure their medicines are making the situation better not worse. Here are three ways scientists, engineers and talent across the company are using innovation to advance processes and technologies that can benefit the long-term health of patients, while also being good for the environment.&lt;/p>"/>
                </block_1>
                <block_2
                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                    sling:resourceType="core/franklin/components/block/v1/block"
                    blockId="\0"
                    classes_customDynamicClass="h5-size,width-large"
                    filter="custom-title"
                    language="none"
                    model="custom-title"
                    modelFields="[title,titleType,classes_customDynamicClass,blockId,classes_commonCustomClass,language,analytics_id]"
                    name="Custom Title"
                    title="Making manufacturing processes greener"
                    titleType="h2"/>
                <block_3
                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                    sling:resourceType="core/franklin/components/block/v1/block"
                    analytics_id="-"
                    blockId="-"
                    classes_customDynamicClass="spacing-bottom,width-large"
                    filter="text-container"
                    language="none"
                    model="text-container"
                    modelFields="[classes_customDynamicClass,blockId,classes_commonCustomClass,language,analytics_id]"
                    name="Text Container">
                    <item_0
                        jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                        sling:resourceType="core/franklin/components/block/v1/block/item"
                        model="text-container-text"
                        modelFields="[text]"
                        name="Text Container Text"
                        text="&lt;p>The complex processes needed to develop medicines often involve many steps, some of which can generate excess landfill or energy waste. At each of these steps, the technology and metrics teams in AbbVie’s Development Sciences organization see opportunities to make improvements that are more environmentally friendly, while maintaining or exceeding high standards for performance, safety and quality.&lt;/p>&lt;p>On the metrics side, scientists employ a tool to assess how green different steps of a given process are based on the materials used.&lt;/p>&lt;p>&quot;The metrics tool allows us to track process performance over time and this will help us identify areas where we can minimize material usage, cut down process steps and still remain efficient,&quot; said Wakuna Galega, senior scientist and metrics team lead, AbbVie.&lt;/p>&lt;p>These insights are then used by the technology team to identify in-house technologies or alternate approaches that could help make the process more robust, consistent, efficient – and greener.&lt;/p>"/>
                </block_3>
                <block_4
                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                    sling:resourceType="core/franklin/components/block/v1/block"
                    attributionName="Eric Moschetta"
                    attributionRole="senior scientist and technology team lead, AbbVie"
                    backgroundImageAlt="\0"
                    blockId="\0"
                    classes_contentAlignment="quote-align-none"
                    classes_contentWidth="quote-content-col-none"
                    classes_theme="quote-none"
                    customClass="\0"
                    id="\0"
                    language="quote-standard,quote-h4"
                    model="quote"
                    modelFields="[quoteVariant,quotation,attributionName,attributionRole,attributionImage,attributionImageMimeType,quoteFragment,backgroundImage,backgroundImageAlt,backgroundImageMimeType,classes_customDynamicClass,blockId,classes_commonCustomClass,language,analytics_id]"
                    name="Quote"
                    quotation="&lt;p>Our focus is to be more proactive, so that years from now, greenness or sustainability becomes an organic part of how we develop processes.&lt;/p>"
                    quoteVariant="quote-standard"/>
                <block_5
                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                    sling:resourceType="core/franklin/components/block/v1/block"
